\\"text\\\":\\\"**Understanding Scala 3 @static**\\\\n\\\\nI’m exploring the @static annotation in Scala 3. When applied to a method in the `JavaSingletonConfiguredExtensionId` object, it generates a static method in that companion class. The private constructor means the ExtensionImpl uses reflection to invoke the method, not the constructor. I'm wondering about the fully qualified class name (FQCN) in the config. It seems that if `dynamicAccess.getObjectFor` tries appending `$`, it might work since there's a companion object. I might need to inspect `DynamicAccess` for clarity.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_ysmbmYSJiZsEW37jJ9mFaMTq|fc_05bd44f533c2786b0169fd62a73cec819dadb5aaa58b3fa14b\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"rg \\\"def getObjectFor|class ReflectiveDynamicAccess|trait DynamicAccess\\\" -n /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge5/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.apache.pekko | head -50\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1506, \"output\": 991, \"cacheRead\": 16384, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 18881, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778213525050, \"responseId\": \"resp_05bd44f533c2786b0169fd62958a50819db1a5abb93af2d678\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_ysmbmYSJiZsEW37jJ9mFaMTq|fc_05bd44f533c2786b0169fd62a73cec819dadb5aaa58b3fa14b\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"(no output)\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778213543742}]}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor-typed_3:1.0.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-08T04-15-01-606202Z.log:1364:[tool-call] delta {\"command\":\"find tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-actor-typed_3/1.0.1/build/native -maxdepth 4 -type f | head -50 && find tests/src/org.apach